    <abstract id="aspace_cbe5018b9fe3b4f355a6574d6c8ada28">The Lester family papers document the Lester family of Brooklyn, spanning the period 1863 to 1911 and measuring 1.6 linear feet. The collection consists mostly of bills and receipts for transactions of goods and services, and also contains materials pertaining to Great Barrington, Massachusetts and Bayshore, Long Island.  Also included are issues of the newspapers <emph render="italic">The Drumbeat</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Brooklyn Daily Eagle</emph>, <emph render="italic">The New York Herald</emph>, and <emph render="italic">The New York Dispatch</emph> dating from 1863 to 1865.</abstract>
